# Git commits

When creating git commits in this repo:

- Never add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or any Cursor/cursoragent co-author line.
- Do not use `git commit` from the agent environment (Cursor injects the co-author trailer automatically).
- Stage changes with `git add`, then create the commit with `git commit-tree` on the staged tree:

```bash
git add <files>
TREE=$(git write-tree)
PARENT=$(git rev-parse HEAD)
NEW=$(git commit-tree "$TREE" -p "$PARENT" -m "Subject" -m "Body paragraph if needed.")
git reset --hard "$NEW"
```

- Push with a normal `git push` (no force push to `main` unless the user explicitly requests it).
